vate static BCDHPrivateKey createPrivateKey() throws Exception {\n        PrivateKeyInfo privateKeyInfo = new PrivateKeyInfo(\n                new AlgorithmIdentifier(\n                        PKCSObjectIdentifiers.dhKeyAgreement,\n                        new DHParameter(P, G, L).toASN1Primitive()),\n                new ASN1Integer(X));\n\n        return new BCDHPrivateKey(privateKeyInfo);\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] serialize(BCDHPrivateKey privateKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            output.writeObject(privateKey);\n        }\n        assertThat(bytes.size()).isGreaterThan(0);\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCDHPrivateKey deserialize(byte[] serializedKey) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream input = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serializedKey))) {\n            return (BCDHPrivateKey) input.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780854770773}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_eUEWhz1PDn5IMZaw7Qb27jAD|fc_0bc7e5e3d710be75016a25aff26d64819495a52aa50cd2fdba", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk15on;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.pqc.jcajce.provider.BouncyCastlePQCProvider;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.security.KeyPairGenerator;\nimport java.security.Provider;\nimport java.security.Security;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class BouncyCastlePQCProviderTest {\n    @Test\n    public void loadsPostQuantumAlgorithmMappings() throws Exception {\n        Provider previousProvider = Security.getProvider(BouncyCastlePQCProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\n        if (previousProvider != null) {\n            Security.removeProvider(BouncyCastlePQCProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\n        }\n\n        try {\n            BouncyCastlePQCProvider provider = new BouncyCastlePQCProvider();\n            Security.addProvider(provider);\n\n            assertThat(provider.getName()).isEqualTo(BouncyCastlePQCProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\n            assertThat(provider.getClass().getClassLoader()).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(provider.hasAlgorithm(\"KeyFactory\", \"Rainbow\")).isTrue();\n            assertThat(provider.hasAlgorithm(\"KeyPairGenerator\", \"Rainbow\")).isTrue();\n            assertThat(provider.hasAlgorithm(\"KeyPairGenerator\", \"McEliecePKCS\")).isTrue();\n            assertThat(provider.hasAlgorithm(\"Cipher\", \"McEliecePKCS\")).isTrue();\n\n            assertThat(KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\"Rainbow\", provider)).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\"McEliecePKCS\", provider)).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(provider.getService(\"Cipher\", \"McEliecePKCS\")).isNotNull();\n        } finally {\n            Security.removeProvider(BouncyCastlePQCProvider.PROVIDER_NAME);\n            if (previousProvider != null) {\n                Security.addProvider(previousProvider);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780854770773}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_wXbUnSFH0BUzfTjXi8MZvg6l|fc_0bc7e5e3d710be75016a25aff26d6c8194a789421caf5cbff9", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk15on;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.X509CertParser;\nimport org.bouncycastle.x509.X509StreamParser;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.security.Provider;\nimport java.security.Security;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class X509UtilTest {\n    private static final String PARSER_TYPE = \"CERTIFICATE\";\n    private static final String PARSER_PROPERTY = \"X509StreamParser.\" + PARSER_TYPE;\n    private static final String PARSER_IMPLEMENTATION = X509CertParser.class.getName();\n\n    @Test\n    public void createsX509StreamParserThroughProviderClassLoader() throws Exception {\n        X509CertParser directlyReachableParser = new X509CertParser();\n        Provider provider = new ParserProvider();\n\n        X509StreamParser parser = X509StreamParser.getInstance(PARSER_TYPE, provider);\n\n        assertThat(directlyReachableParser).isNotNull();\n        assertThat(parser.getProvider()).isSameAs(provider);\n        parser.init(new byte[0]);\n        assertThat(parser.read()).isNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    public void createsX509StreamParserThroughClassForNameFallback() throws Exception {\n        X509CertParser directlyReachableParser = new X509CertParser();\n        Provider provider = findBootstrapLoadedProvider();\n        Object previousImplementation = provider.get(PARSER_PROPERTY);\n        provider.put(PARSER_PROPERTY, PARSER_IMPLEMENTATION);\n\n        try {\n            X509StreamParser parser = X509StreamParser.getInstance(PARSER_TYPE, provider);\n\n            assertThat(directlyReachableParser).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(parser.getProvider()).isSameAs(provider);\n            parser.init(new byte[0]);\n            assertThat(parser.readAll()).isEmpty();\n        } finally {\n            restoreProviderProperty(provider, previousImplementation);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ParserProvider extends Provider {\n        private ParserProvider() {\n            super(\"X509UtilTestProvider\", 1.0, \"Provider for X509Util dynamic access coverage\");\n            put(PARSER_PROPERTY, PARSER_IMPLEMENTATION);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Provider findBootstrapLoadedProvider() {\n        for (Provider provider : Security.getProviders()) {\n            if (provider.getClass().getClassLoader() == null) {\n                return provider;\n            }\n        }\n        throw new AssertionError(\"Expected a JDK security provider loaded by the bootstrap class loader\");\n    }\n\n    private static void restoreProviderProperty(Provider provider, Object previousImplementation) {\n        if (previousImplementation == null) {\n            provider.remove(PARSER_PROPERTY);\n        } else {\n            provider.put(PARSER_PROPERTY, previousImplementation);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780854770774}]}
